        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1883-01-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1883-01-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="280" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d280">
                <head>No. 280.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">West</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Frelinghuysen</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1883-01-15">
                            <hi rend="italic">January</hi> 15,
                                1883</date>. (Received January 16.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to your note of the 28th of
                            November last, relative to the decree of the Venezuelan Government
                            requiring ships papers to be deposited with the port officers, I have
                            the honor to inform you that Harl Granville, in thanking you for this
                            communication, has requested me to state to you that, no report on the
                            subject having been received . from Her Majesty’s legation or consulate
                            in Venezuela, instructions have been sent to inquire into the matter,
                            and that in the meanwhile Her Majesty’s minister will act in concert
                            with the representative of the United States and the representatives of
                            any other powers who maybe taking steps to prevent inconvenience to
                            vessels of their country which may frequent Venezuelan ports.</p>
                <p>I have, &amp;c.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>L. S. SACKVILLE WEST.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
